property.name: description
property.value: This is where [[Clover]] exits from the [[Dark Ruins]]. Once they do, there is no way to go back.

property.name: page
property.value: Dark Ruins

property.name: description
property.value: There is where [[Flowey]] asks [[Clover]] if they are called Gun-Hat. On a [[Genocide Route]], he tells them that nobody will remember their deeds from that point.

property.name: description
property.value: This large rock blocks the entrance to a cave entrance. [[Red Miner]] gets sent to clear it out, but they procrastinate on the job.

property.name: description
property.value: At this point, [[Clover]] sees [[Martlet]] for the first time as she finishes recalibrating a puzzle. She leaves without seeing them.

property.name: description
property.value: After exiting the room from the right of this point into the room to the left of this point, and the [[Fun Value]] is between 30 and 39 (12.35% chance), [[Clover]] gets transported to a different room with one of two NPCs.

property.name: page
property.value: Jane Doe and Wanda

property.name: description
property.value: The Honeydew Resort is a place where [[Clover]] can rest, buy items from the [[Honeydew Shopkeeper]], find the [[Golden Coffee]] and [[Band Merch Pin]] items and advance the [[Slurpy]] quest. The arrows on top of its roof are pointing towards the secret room entrance!

property.name: page
property.value: Honeydew Resort

property.name: description
property.value: Here is the second point that [[Clover]] sees [[Martlet]]. She is hammering in the sign to the right and leaves without seeing Clover.

property.name: description
property.value: Here, [[Clover]] takes the UG Aviator ride to [[Hotland]], [[Martlet]] accompanying if she was spared. However, their ride goes awry and Clover ends up at the [[Dunes]] instead, together with Ava's debris.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Martlet]]'s journal lies in front of her house, where she talks about how she found a job, a hobby, and her mentor, [[Chujin]].

property.name: description
property.value: During [[Martlet]]'s [[Genocide Route]] [[Martlet/In Battle|battle]], a cutscene plays between her two phases where [[Chujin]] and her talk about her new job at the Royal Guard.

property.name: description
property.value: After initially visiting Snowdin, this bridge is broken, and Martlet's house cannot be reached. After getting the ability to [[Fast Travel]], [[Clover]] can go back to [[Snowdin]] and revisit this place. The bridge will be fixed and they can access (the entrance to) Martlet's house.

property.name: description
property.value: After getting the ability to [[Fast Travel]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], a [[Sweet Corn]] waits here for her siblings to get out of the [[Dark Ruins]] and challenges [[Clover]] to hug someone before they leave.

property.name: page
property.value: Sweet Corn#Pacifist Route

properties.property:
A pair of NPCs lost in Snowdin on a honeymoon. You can exchange a [[Snowdin Map]] for [[Matches]] with them.
Next stop in the [[Slurpy]] puzzle: the [[Maury]] NPC to the east of [[Honeydew Resort]]!

property.name: description
property.value: This miner from the [[East Mines]] comes here to mine this big rock after [[Clover]] gets the ability to [[Fast Travel]]. However, they are procrastinating on the job.

property.name: page
property.value: Red Miner

property.name: description
property.value: After getting the ability to [[Fast Travel]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], Penilla can be found here admiring the frozen lake view.

property.name: page
property.value: Penilla#Pacifist Route

property.name: description
property.value: After three dogs dared him to lick this pole, Slurpy got stuck. To help him, the next stop is retrieving the [[Honeydew Coffee]] from the [[Honeydew Shopkeeper]] and giving it to the [[Maury]] NPC to the east of the [[Honeydew Resort]].

property.name: description
property.value: After the battle with [[Martlet]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], Frostermit appears here as an NPC, talking about how it wants to move to the [[Wild East]].

property.name: page
property.value: Frostermit#Main Story

property.name: description
property.value: After getting the ability to [[Fast Travel]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], Flier appears here after helping [[Dalv]] move. His house business, unfortunately, isn't going very well.

property.name: page
property.value: Flier#Pacifist Route

property.name: description
property.value: After getting the ability to [[Fast Travel]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], Dalv appears here with [[Pops]], intending to move from [[Dark Ruins]] to this dilapidated shack.

property.name: page
property.value: Dalv#Pacifist Route

property.name: description
property.value: After the battle with [[Martlet]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], Know Cone appears here, planning to climb a big hill to see [[Hotland]].

property.name: page
property.value: Know Cone#Main Story

property.name: description
property.value: This NPC quotes some books they read on pressing X to slow down, eating to stay healthy, and running out of book quotes.

property.name: page
property.value: Awkward Guy

property.name: description
property.value: After the battle with [[Martlet]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], this trio appears as NPCs, each with their own concerns.

property.name: page
property.value: Trihecta#Main Story

property.name: description
property.value: A cameo of Ice Wolf from ''[[ut:Undertale|Undertale]]'', they appear to be doing the same job in ''[[Undertale Yellow]]'', which is throwing ice cubes into a river.

property.name: page
property.value: Ice Wolf

property.name: description
property.value: This bear has fallen asleep in front of the [[Honeydew Resort]] while delivering a shipment.

property.name: description
property.value: This fluffy monster is here just to avoid their job responsibilities!

property.name: description
property.value: They never heard of [[The Shufflers]], and plan to listen to [[Rodney's Band]] but never do.

property.name: page
property.value: Flame Guy

property.name: description
property.value: On a [[Genocide Route]], this log sees everything.

property.name: description
property.value: After getting the ability to [[Fast Travel]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], this mirror monster is back from the [[Dark Ruins]]! He's dreaming of becoming [[Asgore]]'s tailor.

property.name: page
property.value: Rorrim#Pacifist Route

property.name: description
property.value: Several Micro Froggits enjoying their time in their micro hot spring.

property.name: page
property.value: Micro Froggit#Main Story

property.name: description
property.value: This ant-like NPC has lost his [[Soggy Mitten|mitten]]. [[Clover]] can retrieve his mitten from [[Maury]], after giving them a [[Honeydew Coffee]]. Donald gives Clover a [[Snowdin Map]] in return, which Clover can give to the [[Adventurers]] to continue the quest to free [[Slurpy]]!

property.name: page
property.value: Donald Glover

property.name: description
property.value: This crazy conspiracy theorist is upset about the hot spring's asymmetrical placement.

property.name: description
property.value: This flame monster is very happy to have a job as a torch!

property.name: description
property.value: This spherical monster is swimming for their own fitness, remarking that they've dropped a whole goggle size.

property.name: description
property.value: They have long awaited their visit to the hot springs, and are now enjoying their relaxation.

property.name: description
property.value: This rambling monster was told to visit the [[Honeydew Resort]] to relieve stress, but they can't shake off the feeling that they are causing the downfall of the Underground.

property.name: page
property.value: Couch Bear

property.name: description
property.value: This band of monsters represents the three main composers of ''[[Undertale Yellow]]'': [[Master Sword]]/Rodney (center), [[MyNewSoundtrack]] (left) and [[NoteBlock]] (right). They play ''[[Honeydew Cabin]]'', but can be asked to switch their music to ''[[Honeydew Ruins]]'', ''[[Honeydew Snow]]'', ''[[Honeydew Hideaway]]'' or ''[[Honeydew Bark]]''. While playing ''Honeydew Bark'', the [[Superfan]] NPC can give [[Clover]] a [[Band Merch Pin]].

property.name: page
property.value: Rodney's Band

property.name: description
property.value: This NPC is a great fan of [[Rodney's Band]], and used to follow them around the Underground. If [[Clover]] asks Rodney to change the music to ''[[Honeydew Bark]]'', this NPC gives them a [[Band Merch Pin]].

property.name: description
property.value: This rabbit-like NPC came from the [[Dunes]] to try the [[Honeydew Pancake]]s.

property.name: page
property.value: Dunes Rabbit

property.name: description
property.value: This NPC is too lazy to move. [[Clover]] can exchange a [[Honeydew Coffee]] with them for a [[Soggy Mitten]], and later [[Matches]] for a [[Lukewarm Coffee]], that they can use to free [[Slurpy]]. Maury still does not move at this point; they have frozen solid.

property.name: description
property.value: This old lady does not like the Royal Guard messing with the bridge.

property.name: description
property.value: This completely stationary snowflake has trouble melting.

property.name: description
property.value: After [[Martlet]]'s battle on a [[Pacifist Route]], Insomnitot appears here in an endless cycle of attempting to sleep.

property.name: page
property.value: Insomnitot#Main Story

property.name: description
property.value: After getting the ability to [[Fast Travel]] on a [[Pacifist Route]], Crispy Scroll can be found by the docks. He is disappointed by the lack of anime to be found at the [[Garbage Dump]].

property.name: page
property.value: Crispy Scroll#Pacifist Route

property.name: description
property.value: Depending on the [[Fun Value]], one of two NPCs appear here. Jane Doe, a deer-like monster, is searching for a resident who went missing. Wanda, a unicorn-like monster, appears to have wandered here due to her boyfriend not paying attention to her.

property.name: page
property.value: Jane Doe and Wanda

property.name: description
property.value: [[Martlet]]'s first molten rock puzzle. To solve this one, control the wheels using left and right arrow keys, and don't let the ball hit the planks!

property.name: description
property.value: In this puzzle, [[Clover]] must time their crossing over the bridge while several of its planks swing up and down. Otherwise, they fall down to the pillow below.

property.name: description
property.value: Similarly to the first molten rock puzzle, move the platforms up and down to navigate the ball towards the ice cube at the bottom.

property.name: description
property.value: The first station of the Underground Postal Service! [[Mail Whale]] arrives here to give [[Clover]] the [[Mail#Intro Letter|Intro Letter]].

property.name: page
property.value: Underground Postal Service

properties.property: "(The original text of this sign was crossed out.) (Now it reads "Entry Forbidden" in blue crayon.)"

"This is a box. It is a stupid box. You can put items in it and they'll stay there. Until you take it out that is, then it's not there. And then there are more of these boxes later. You can use them to retrieve the stuff you put it this box. It's super dumb. Sincerely, a box hater."

"To whom it may concern: In accordance with Royal Guard guide book section four, paragraph two, This puzzle is intended to impede the progress of an intruder (probably you), Entertain the residents of the surrounding area (Snowdin), And appear intimidating to would-be intruders or wrong-doers, (I'm unclear on what they mean by that, just go with it.) To pass by this challenge, you must melt the icecube. Make sure the ball-thing gets to the bottom without breaking though. Signed: Martlet of the Underground Royal Guard" [Sign continues with a P.S., P.P.S., P.P.P.S. and P.P.P.P.S.]

"Dear owners of dilapidated cabin: First, I am very sorry that your cabin is so dilapidated. Like, I don't know what happened to it, but I'm sure it was unfortunate. Second, I am sorry that some of your wood has gone missing. According to the Royal Guard guide book section forty-two, paragraph one, So long as notice is given to the original owner at least two business days prior, Any and all eyesores can be repurposed for puzzles or other diversions. Well, I didn't know how to contact you, but consider this notice! ...Unfortunately not of the prior variety, but you know... notice."
"Welcome to the Honeydew Resort! North: The Honeydew Lodge Northwest: The Honeydew Hotspring East: Exit to Snowdin"

properties.property: "(Nice and cozy!) (You notice a sticker on the heater.) Crafted with love by Chujin & Martlet!"
"Honeydew Resort: Family owned and operated All travelers are welcome!"

properties.property: "To whom it may concern: After building the first ball puzzle, I realized a fatal flaw in its design. How was an intruder supposed to like, see it? The puzzle was on a higher plain, out of your average monster's eyesight. If someone solved that puzzle, they must be very good at guessing. In any case, I have created an improved version! With a new vertical design, you can see what you're controlling! The parts may still get stuck though. Please refer to my instructions back at the first puzzle if that happens. Signed: Martlet of the Underground Royal Guard"
